Exercise 13.12: How many destructor calls occur in the following code
fragment?

bool fcn(const Sales_data *trans, Sales_data accum)
{
    Sales_data item1(*trans), item2(accum);
    return item1.isbn() != item2.isbn();
}

Answer:
There are 3 destructor calls when we exit fcn, 2 calls for item1 and item2 since they are defined locally
when we exit fcn their destructor will be called, in addition since accum is copied by value
it will be destroyed when exiting fcn.
Since trans is a recived as a pointer the Sales_data object it points to will not be destroyed.

